Richard B. Johnson" <root@chaos.analogic.com>:
....
>int main()
>{
>   int xxx = 1;
>
>   printf("%08x (%d)\n", xxx, xxx);
>   xxx <<= 31;
>   printf("%08x (%d)\n", xxx, xxx);
>   xxx >>= 31;
>   printf("%08x (%d)\n", xxx, xxx);
>   return 0;
>}
># gcc -O2 -o xxx xxx.c
#> ./xxx
>00000001 (1)
>80000000 (-2147483648)
>ffffffff (-1)
># exit
Is true for signed integers. Unsigned integers do get a logical shift:
00000001 (1)
80000000 (-2147483648)
00000001 (1)
